19#include <sys/types.h>
20
21#include <stdlib.h>
22
23#include "tmux.h"
24
25/*
26 * Rename a window.
27 */
28
29static enum cmd_retval cmd_rename_window_exec(struct cmd *,
30 struct cmdq_item *);
31
32const struct cmd_entry cmd_rename_window_entry = {
33 .name = "rename-window",
34 .alias = "renamew",
35
36 .args = { "t:", 1, 1 },
37 .usage = CMD_TARGET_WINDOW_USAGE " new-name",
38
39 .target = { 't', CMD_FIND_WINDOW, 0 },
40
41 .flags = CMD_AFTERHOOK,
42 .exec = cmd_rename_window_exec
43};
44
45static enum cmd_retval
46cmd_rename_window_exec(struct cmd *self, struct cmdq_item *item)
47{
48 struct args *args = self->args;
49 struct client *c = cmd_find_client(item, NULL, 1);
50 struct session *s = item->target.s;
51 struct winlink *wl = item->target.wl;
52 char *newname;
53
54 newname = format_single(item, args->argv[0], c, s, wl, NULL);
55 window_set_name(wl->window, newname);
56 options_set_number(wl->window->options, "automatic-rename", 0);
57
58 server_status_window(wl->window);
59 free(newname);
60
61 return (CMD_RETURN_NORMAL);
62}
